TITLE: Converting Animated GIF to Animated WebP with Sharp (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Example placeholder for converting an animated GIF to an animated WebP format using Sharp. The actual code implementation is not provided in the given documentation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/lovell/sharp/blob/main/docs/src/content/docs/api-constructor.md#2025-04-22_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// Convert an animated GIF to an animated WebP
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Using MozJPEG Optimization with Sharp
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to enable MozJPEG optimization in Sharp to reduce JPEG file size. MozJPEG applies trellis quantization, overshoot deringing, optimized scans, and uses quantization table 3 for better compression at the cost of slower processing.
SOURCE: https://github.com/lovell/sharp/blob/main/docs/src/content/docs/api-output.md#2025-04-22_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// Use mozjpeg to reduce output JPEG file size (slower)
const data = await sharp(input)
  .jpeg({ mozjpeg: true })
  .toBuffer();
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Applying Convolution with Custom Kernel in Sharp
DESCRIPTION: Convolves the image with a specified kernel. Requires kernel dimensions, values, and optional scale and offset. Useful for various image processing operations like edge detection or blurring.
SOURCE: https://github.com/lovell/sharp/blob/main/docs/src/content/docs/api-operation.md#2025-04-22_snippet_16

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
sharp(input)
  .convolve({
    width: 3,
    height: 3,
    kernel: [-1, 0, 1, -2, 0, 2, -1, 0, 1]
  })
  .raw()
  .toBuffer(function(err, data, info) {
    // data contains the raw pixel data representing the convolution
    // of the input image with the horizontal Sobel operator
  });
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Preserving All Metadata in Sharp
DESCRIPTION: Keeps all metadata (EXIF, ICC, XMP, IPTC) from the input image in the output image. Overrides the default behavior of converting to sRGB color space and stripping all metadata.
SOURCE: https://github.com/lovell/sharp/blob/main/docs/src/content/docs/api-output.md#2025-04-22_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const outputWithMetadata = await sharp(inputWithMetadata)
  .keepMetadata()
  .toBuffer();
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Removing Alpha Channel in Sharp
DESCRIPTION: Removes the alpha channel from an image using Sharp. This operation is a no-op if the image doesn't have an alpha channel.
SOURCE: https://github.com/lovell/sharp/blob/main/docs/src/content/docs/api-channel.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
sharp('rgba.png')
  .removeAlpha()
  .toFile('rgb.png', function(err, info) {
    // rgb.png is a 3 channel image without an alpha channel
  });
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Applying Affine Transformation to an Image with Sharp
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to perform an affine transform on an image with customizable options including background color and interpolator. This transform applies a 2x2 matrix to manipulate the image coordinates.
SOURCE: https://github.com/lovell/sharp/blob/main/docs/src/content/docs/api-operation.md#2025-04-22_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const pipeline = sharp()
  .affine([[1, 0.3], [0.1, 0.7]], {
     background: 'white',
     interpolator: sharp.interpolators.nohalo
  })
  .toBuffer((err, outputBuffer, info) => {
     // outputBuffer contains the transformed image
     // info.width and info.height contain the new dimensions
  });

inputStream
  .pipe(pipeline);
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Retrieving Image Statistics
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to access channel-wise statistics and opacity information using Sharp's stats() method.
SOURCE: https://github.com/lovell/sharp/blob/main/docs/src/content/docs/api-input.md#2025-04-22_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const image = sharp(inputJpg);
image
  .stats()
  .then(function(stats) {
     // stats contains the channel-wise statistics array and the isOpaque value
  });
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Unflattening Image to Add Alpha Channel in Sharp
DESCRIPTION: Ensures the image has an alpha channel with all white pixel values made fully transparent. Existing alpha channel values for non-white pixels remain unchanged. This feature is experimental.
SOURCE: https://github.com/lovell/sharp/blob/main/docs/src/content/docs/api-operation.md#2025-04-22_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
await sharp(rgbInput)
  .unflatten()
  .toBuffer();
```

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
await sharp(rgbInput)
  .threshold(128, { grayscale: false }) // converter bright pixels to white
  .unflatten()
  .toBuffer();
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Flattening Alpha Channel with Background Color in Sharp
DESCRIPTION: Merges the alpha transparency channel with a specified background color, then removes the alpha channel. The background color defaults to black but can be customized using the 'color' module.
SOURCE: https://github.com/lovell/sharp/blob/main/docs/src/content/docs/api-operation.md#2025-04-22_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
await sharp(rgbaInput)
  .flatten({ background: '#F0A703' })
  .toBuffer();
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Basic Image Composition with Multiple Layers
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates compositing multiple image layers with different gravity positions onto a background image.
SOURCE: https://github.com/lovell/sharp/blob/main/docs/src/content/docs/api-composite.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
await sharp(background)
  .composite([
    { input: layer1, gravity: 'northwest' },
    { input: layer2, gravity: 'southeast' },
  ])
  .toFile('combined.png');
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Creating Deep Zoom Tiles with Sharp
DESCRIPTION: Creates a deep zoom image pyramid with 512x512 tiles and outputs to a DZI format. The output includes both the DZI XML definition and the tile files organized by zoom level.
SOURCE: https://github.com/lovell/sharp/blob/main/docs/src/content/docs/api-output.md#2025-04-22_snippet_29

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
sharp('input.tiff')
  .png()
  .tile({
    size: 512
  })
  .toFile('output.dz', function(err, info) {
    // output.dzi is the Deep Zoom XML definition
    // output_files contains 512x512 tiles grouped by zoom level
  });
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Applying Gamma Correction in Sharp
DESCRIPTION: Applies gamma correction to improve perceived brightness of resized images in non-linear color spaces. It reduces encoding pre-resize and increases it post-resize. JPEG and WebP inputs won't use shrink-on-load optimization with gamma correction.
SOURCE: https://github.com/lovell/sharp/blob/main/docs/src/content/docs/api-operation.md#2025-04-22_snippet_12



----------------------------------------

TITLE: Sharpening an Image with Sharp
DESCRIPTION: Shows different ways to sharpen an image, from a simple default sharpening to more advanced options with sigma and controls for flat and jagged areas.
SOURCE: https://github.com/lovell/sharp/blob/main/docs/src/content/docs/api-operation.md#2025-04-22_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const data = await sharp(input).sharpen().toBuffer();
```

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const data = await sharp(input).sharpen({ sigma: 2 }).toBuffer();
```

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const data = await sharp(input)
  .sharpen({
    sigma: 2,
    m1: 0,
    m2: 3,
    x1: 3,
    y2: 15,
    y3: 15,
  })
  .toBuffer();
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Creating IIIF Tiles with Sharp Stream
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates streaming tile generation with IIIF layout using Sharp's pipe functionality.
SOURCE: https://github.com/lovell/sharp/blob/main/docs/src/content/docs/api-output.md#2025-04-22_snippet_31

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const iiififier = sharp().tile({ layout: "iiif" });
readableStream
  .pipe(iiififier)
  .pipe(writeableStream);
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Creating PNG from Raw Pixel Array using Sharp
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to create a PNG image from a raw array of pixel values, specifying dimensions and channels.
SOURCE: https://github.com/lovell/sharp/blob/main/docs/src/content/docs/api-constructor.md#2025-04-22_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const input = Uint8Array.from([255, 255, 255, 0, 0, 0]);
const image = sharp(input, {
  raw: {
    width: 2,
    height: 1,
    channels: 3
  }
});
await image.toFile('my-two-pixels.png');
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Reducing Animated GIF File Size with Sharp
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to apply lossy compression to an animated GIF to reduce file size. This example uses interFrameMaxError to allow some quality loss between frames for better compression.
SOURCE: https://github.com/lovell/sharp/blob/main/docs/src/content/docs/api-output.md#2025-04-22_snippet_20

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// Lossy file size reduction of animated GIF
await sharp('in.gif', { animated: true })
  .gif({ interFrameMaxError: 8 })
  .toFile('optim.gif');
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Converting SVG to LZW-compressed TIFF with reduced bitdepth
DESCRIPTION: Example of converting an SVG input to a TIFF output using LZW compression and reducing to 1 bit per pixel, suitable for simple black and white images.
SOURCE: https://github.com/lovell/sharp/blob/main/docs/src/content/docs/api-output.md#2025-04-22_snippet_23

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// Convert SVG input to LZW-compressed, 1 bit per pixel TIFF output
sharp('input.svg')
  .tiff({
    compression: 'lzw',
    bitdepth: 1
  })
  .toFile('1-bpp-output.tiff')
  .then(info => { ... });
```

